{
  "texts": [
    "They then applied these to predictive modeling tasks, for example the prediction of heart failure, with positive results.",
    "Beam et al developed Cui2vec, applying both Word2Vec and Glove to a massive multimodal medical dataset including structured records as well as unstructured notes and journal articles (Beam et al., 2019).",
    "(2018) developed a time-aware attention mechanism to augment their Continuous Bag Of Words (CBOW) Word2Vec model in order to capture the differences in the length of time that medical conditions last.",
    "Xiang et al. (2019) compared three popular methods of creating embeddings and found Word2Vec to be most effective for predictive modeling tasks.",
    "More recently, following the success of transformer architectures in NLP tasks, researchers have applied these too to the clinical domain."
  ]
}